wiki.content: “Holy Smokes” is the second single from Trippie Redd’s fifth studio album, TRIP AT KNIGHT, and his first collaboration with Philadelphia rapper Lil Uzi Vert. The song was first previewed in early February 2021. As one of the many snippets teased prior to the release of TRIP AT KNIGHT, fans speculated if it would appear on the project. In an Instagram post from May 24, 2021, Trippie asked fans who he should feature on the song. An overwhelming amount of requests for Lil Uzi Vert, some of which Trippie pinned, led fans to speculate a potential feature from Uzi. During a livestream on July 1, 2021, Adin Ross accidentally revealed his involvement in a music video with Trippie and Uzi. Later that night, Trippie showed the “Holy Smokes” music video set on his Instagram Story, confirming the song’s name, placement on TRIP AT KNIGHT, and Lil Uzi Vert’s feature. On July 7, 2021, Trippie announced the song’s release date of July 16, 2021, and previewed part of Uzi’s verse. Trippie officially announced the song’s music video in an Instagram post from July 14, 2021. Read more on Last.fm.
